## Key Paths and JSON Structure

Keys use dot notation that maps directly to nested JSON structure in the backend. Each dot represents a level of nesting:

```lua
-- This key:
FastFlags.Private("UserGenerated.Saves.AutoSavePeriod", Asserts.FinitePositive, 600)
```

Maps to this JSON path:

```json
{
  "UserGenerated": {
    "Saves": {
      "AutoSavePeriod": 600
    }
  }
}
```

### Supported Value Types

Values can be any JSON-encodable data type:

| Type | Lua | JSON | Example |
|------|-----|------|---------|
| Boolean | `true`/`false` | `true`/`false` | `"Enabled": true` |
| Number | `123`, `1.5` | `123`, `1.5` | `"Rate": 0.5` |
| String | `"text"` | `"text"` | `"Level": "Warn"` |
| Null | `nil` | `null` | `"Optional": null` |
| Array | `{1, 2, 3}` | `[1, 2, 3]` | `"Items": [1, 2]` |
| Object | `{a=1, b=2}` | `{"a": 1, "b": 2}` | `"Config": {"x": 1}` |

### Example JSON Structure

```jsonc
{
  "UserGenerated": {
    "Logging": {
      "ClientLevel": "Warn",
      "ServerLevel": "Info"
    },
    "Saves": {
      "Enabled": true,
      "AutoSavePeriod": 600
    },
    "Analytics": {
      "PlayerEventChances": {
        "PlayerDeath": 0.05,
        "PlayerCoinCollected": 0.01
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Corresponding flag registrations:

```lua
FastFlags.Replicated("UserGenerated.Logging.ClientLevel", Asserts.String, "Warn")
FastFlags.Private("UserGenerated.Logging.ServerLevel", Asserts.String, "Info")
FastFlags.Private("UserGenerated.Saves.Enabled", Asserts.Boolean, true)
FastFlags.Private("UserGenerated.Saves.AutoSavePeriod", Asserts.FinitePositive, 600)
FastFlags.Private("UserGenerated.Analytics.PlayerEventChances", 
  Asserts.Map(Asserts.String, Asserts.FiniteNonNegative), 
  {}
)
```

### Key Conflicts

Keys with hierarchical overlap will error. You cannot have both a value and nested object at the same path:

```lua
-- These would conflict:
FastFlags.Private("UserGenerated.Saves", Asserts.Boolean, true)      -- value at Saves
FastFlags.Private("UserGenerated.Saves.Enabled", Asserts.Boolean, true)  -- nested under Saves
-- Error: ConflictingKeys
```

