## Examples

### Private Server Flag

```lua
local SavesEnabled = FastFlags.Private(
  "UserGenerated.Saves.Enabled",
  Asserts.Boolean,
  true
)

if SavesEnabled:Get() then
  -- saves are enabled
end
```

### Replicated Flag (Shared Module)

Place `Replicated` flags in a shared module under ReplicatedStorage. Both server and client require the same module:

```lua
-- ReplicatedStorage/Shared/SomeSharedModule.luau
local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")
local FastFlags = require(ReplicatedStorage.UserGenerated.FastFlags)
local Asserts = require(ReplicatedStorage.UserGenerated.Lang.Asserts)

local LoggingLevel = FastFlags.Replicated(
  "UserGenerated.Logging.ClientLevel",
  Asserts.String,
  "Warn"
)

return {
  LoggingLevel = LoggingLevel,
}
```

Then require from server and client code:

```lua
-- Server or Client script
local SharedModule = require(ReplicatedStorage.Shared.SomeSharedModule)
local level = SharedModule.LoggingLevel:Get()
SharedModule.LoggingLevel.Changed:Connect(function(curr)
  -- react to changes
end)
```

The server must require the module first so replication is set up before clients connect.

### Reacting to Changes

```lua
local AutoSavePeriod = FastFlags.Private(
  "UserGenerated.Saves.AutoSavePeriod",
  Asserts.FinitePositive,
  900
)

-- Initial setup
ProfileStore.SetConstant("AUTO_SAVE_PERIOD", AutoSavePeriod:Get())

-- React to runtime changes
AutoSavePeriod.Changed:Connect(function(curr)
  ProfileStore.SetConstant("AUTO_SAVE_PERIOD", curr)
end)
```

### Waiting for Load

```lua
-- Wait for system to load
FastFlags.Loaded:Wait()

-- Or wait for a specific flag to load
local SomeFlag = FastFlags.Private("Game.SomeFlag", Asserts.Boolean, false)
local value = SomeFlag:GetAsync() -- yields until this flag loads
```

### Table Values

```lua
local ABTestDefaults = FastFlags.Replicated(
  "UserGenerated.ABTestDefaults",
  Asserts.Map(Asserts.String, Asserts.Any),
  {}
)

local defaults = ABTestDefaults:Get()
```

### Full Pattern with Change Handling

```lua
local ReplicatedStorage = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")
local FastFlags = require(ReplicatedStorage.UserGenerated.FastFlags)
local Asserts = require(ReplicatedStorage.UserGenerated.Lang.Asserts)

local SpawnRate = FastFlags.Replicated(
  "Game.SpawnRate",
  Asserts.FinitePositive,
  5.0
)

-- Initial setup using async to ensure loaded value
local rate = SpawnRate:GetAsync()
ConfigureSpawner(rate)

-- React to live updates
SpawnRate.Changed:Connect(function(current, previous)
  ConfigureSpawner(current)
end)
```
